---
/**
 * The guided walk — chapter index / hub. Lists the on-ramp, the five teaching
 * chapters, and the close, with each chapter's anchor record and the skill it
 * teaches. Live chapters link out; the rest are marked drafting.
 */
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import { WALK_CHAPTERS, WALK_START_HREF, walkHref } from "../../lib/walk";
import { withBase } from "../../lib/site";
---

<Base
  title="The guided walk"
  section="home"
  description="The narrative spine over the BOSC record: five chapters that tell the story and teach you to read the documents."
>
  <div class="walk-onramp">
    <p><a href={WALK_START_HREF}>← Start here</a></p>
    <div class="walk-kicker">Project BOSC · guided walk</div>
    <h1>The walk, chapter by chapter</h1>
    <p class="walk-onramp-lead">
      Five chapters, ordered cause → consequence. Each advances the story and
      teaches one record-reading skill, anchored to a real document you can open
      and check. Follow it straight through, or drop into any chapter and peel off
      into the library when something catches your eye.
    </p>

    <ol class="walk-chapters walk-chapters--full">
      {
        WALK_CHAPTERS.map((c) => (
          <li class:list={["walk-chapter", !c.live && "is-draft"]}>
            <span class="walk-step-badge">{c.step}</span>
            <span class="walk-chapter-main">
              {c.live ? (
                <a class="walk-chapter-title" href={walkHref(c.slug)}>{c.title}</a>
              ) : (
                <span class="walk-chapter-title">{c.title} <span class="walk-draft-tag">drafting</span></span>
              )}
              <span class="walk-chapter-skill">{c.skill}</span>
              <span class="walk-chapter-anchor">Anchor: {c.anchor}</span>
            </span>
            {c.live && <a class="walk-chapter-go" href={walkHref(c.slug)} aria-label={`Read chapter ${c.step}`}>→</a>}
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ol>

    <p class="stub-note">
      Chapter 4 (“What it costs the public”) is built and demonstrates the Record
      Teardown teaching pattern end to end. The other chapters are authored in the
      spine and land as their anchor records are wired to live teardowns. You can
      also preview the teardown component on its own
      <a href={withBase("/site/teardown-showcase")}>here</a>.
    </p>

    <div class="walk-cta">
      <a class="btn" href={walkHref("cost")}>Read the built chapter →</a>
      <a class="walk-cta-secondary" href={withBase("/site/")}>or browse the archive</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
